{
  "text": "In Jain et al. [CITATION_1] , deformable templates are employed for object detection. Here, prior knowledge of an object shape is described by a prototype template which consists of the representative contour/edges, and a set of probabilistic deformation transformations on the template. A Bayesian scheme, which is based on this prior knowledge and the edge information in the input image, is used to find a match between the deformed template and objects in the image.",
